result.name: Red Seasons Restaurant

reviews.text: A very non-contempory local Chinese restaurant.  Or you may call it a typical local "kaifong" (neighborhood) restaurant which wins your visit by food, not by decorations and service. I don't mean their service is bad but just don't expect too much.  Seating is comfortable although decorations primitive.  Must order dishes are bbq pork and bbq suckling pig, feeling freshly made and very tasty.  Believe it or not, they are made in underground stone stove.  Delivery is fast within minutes.
If u want to taste traditional dishes in Hong Kong,.u must come here, u can't have it outside easily
I went here for my relative's birthday. We had many dishes including scallops roast goose and roast chicken. The poultry was tasty - with the chicken being moist. Wasn't the cleanest place but ok.
Good taste and many kind of food
Chinese styled bbq piggy fillet, yummy!
